cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE

This paper is about image segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks and generative adversarial networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an end-to-end synthetic segmentation network, which involves training a segmentation network for a target imaging modality without having manual labels. This involves the use of machine learning techniques such as cycle generative adversarial networks and deep convolutional neural networks, which are covered in categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed approach on two experiments involving abdominal and brain images, which are covered in categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CV.
